                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_269-item1">
                     <author key="person_56731778" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/56731778/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ḥāfiẓ, 14th cent.</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Ḥāfiẓ Shīrāzī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Shams al-Dīn Muḥammad Shīrāzī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">‏حافظ شيرازى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_72">Dīvān-i Ḥāfiẓ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_72">دیوان حافظ</title>
                     <note>F1a. a) Impression of small square seal of 'Abbas 'Ali al-Husaini, dated 1169 (1755-6). b) Note of purchase for 100 sikkah rupees. F186b. Note of possession by Dhu 'l-Fiqar Beg, wishing for anyone claiming the book to be sent blind. Written twice. Following folio, recto: impression of the same seal as on f1a. Ruled margins and dividing panels. Some final verses in red. Illuminated initial opening. Five miniature paintings, probably Kashmir work. I (f31a), a lover's drinkimg party; 2 (f75a), dervishes dancing; 3 (f98a), alfresco drinking party; 4 (f133a), polo match; 5 (f147a), drinking and reading by a stream.</note>
                     <incipit>Ala ya ayyuha 'l-saqi</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>As for Codrington/Reade No 265.</bibl>
                        <bibl>General Gordon's bequest of books and Turkish, Persian and Arabic manuscripts is mentioned, without details in the donations register under November 6 1841. The bequest is mentioned in J.R.A.S., vii, 1843, Annual Report, p. x, and the manuscripts are briefly listed in the Proceedings, pp. xxx-xxxi.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
